{"title_page": "1912 Liga Peruana de Football", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n  | competition        = [[Peruvian Primera Divisi\u00f3n]]\n  | season             = 1912\n  | winners            = [[Lima Cricket and Football Club|Lima Cricket]]<br>1st Primera Divisi\u00f3n title\n  | runners-up         = [[Ciclista Lima|Association]]\n  | relegated          = \n  | continentalcup1    = \n  | continentalcup1 qualifiers = \n  | continentalcup2    = \n  | continentalcup2 qualifiers = \n  | continentalcup3    = \n  | continentalcup3 qualifiers = \n  | league topscorer   = \n  | biggest home win   = \n  | biggest away win   = \n  | highest scoring    = \n  | total goals        = \n  | average goals      = \n  | longest wins       = \n  | longest unbeaten   = \n  | longest losses     = \n  | highest attendance = \n  | lowest attendance  = \n  | average attendance = \n  | prevseason         = \n  | nextseason         = [[1913 Liga Peruana de Football|1913]]\n}}\nThe '''1912 [[Peruvian Primera Divisi\u00f3n|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]]''' was the first season of top-flight Peruvian football. A total of 16 teams competed in the league, The champion was [[Lima Cricket and Football Club|Lima Cricket]]. This first season with organised league, covering [[Lima]], [[Callao]], and suburbs such as [[Miraflores District, Lima|Miraflores]] and [[Barranco District|Barranco]]. [[Sport Jos\u00e9 G\u00e1lvez|Jos\u00e9 G\u00e1lvez]] de Lima withdrew because of not agreeing with the competition format. The clubs from Callao (among which [[Atl\u00e9tico Chalaco]]) did not respond to the invitation to enter. The 16 teams were divided over a first and a second level, both of 8 clubs. Cricket and [[Ciclista Lima|Association]] finished equal on points; Cricket were declared champions on head-to-head record; Escuela Militar de Chorrillos withdrew halfway through the season when positioned last in the Primera Divisi\u00f3n with a single point. The first match was played on 5 May 1912 between Lima Cricket and Sport Vitarte. The match was a 6\u20131 win for Lima Cricket.\n\n==League table==\n===First Division===\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=QR\n|winpoints=2\n\n|team1=LCR|name_LCR=[[Lima Cricket and Football Club|Lima Cricket]]\n|team2=CIC|name_CIC=[[Ciclista Lima|Association]]\n|team3=JC1|name_JC1=[[Jorge Ch\u00e1vez No. 1|Jorge Ch\u00e1vez]]\n|team4=ALI|name_ALI=[[Alianza Lima|Sport Alianza]]\n|team5=MIR|name_MIR=[[Miraflores Sporting]]\n|team6=INC|name_INC=[[Sport Inca]]\n|team7=VIT|name_VIT=[[Sport Vitarte]]\n|team8=MCH|name_MCH=[[Escuela Militar de Chorrillos]]\n|win_LCR=1|draw_LCR=0|loss_LCR=0|gf_LCR=6|ga_LCR=1\n|win_CIC=0|draw_CIC=0|loss_CIC=1|gf_CIC=0|ga_CIC=1\n|win_JC1=1|draw_JC1=0|loss_JC1=0|gf_JC1=2|ga_JC1=0\n|win_ALI=0|draw_ALI=0|loss_ALI=1|gf_ALI=0|ga_ALI=2\n|win_MIR=2|draw_MIR=0|loss_MIR=0|gf_MIR=3|ga_MIR=0\n|win_INC=1|draw_INC=0|loss_INC=0|gf_INC=1|ga_INC=0\n|win_VIT=0|draw_VIT=0|loss_VIT=2|gf_VIT=1|ga_VIT=7\n|win_MCH=0|draw_MCH=0|loss_MCH=1|gf_MCH=0|ga_MCH=2\n|hth_LCR=LIMA 5\u20130 AFBC; AFBC 0\u20131 LIMA\n|hth_CIC=LCR\n|col_C=#ACE1AF|text_C=\n|result1=C\n|col_RET=inherit|text_RET=Retired\n|result8=RET\n\n|update=complete|source=\n}}\n\n==Title==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0 auto;\"\n|-\n!Liga Peruana de Football <br />1912 Champion\n|-\n|'''[[Lima Cricket and Football Club|Lima Cricket]]'''<br/>'''1st title '''\n|}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesp/peru1912.html Peru 1912 season] at [[RSSSF]]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110715174858/http://www.retrofutbolas.com/Templates/campeonatos.htm Peruvian Championship]\n*[http://sisbib.unmsm.edu.pe/bibVirtual/tesis/Human/Alvarez_E_T/Cap4.htm La Liga Peruana de Football]\n\n{{Primera Divisi\u00f3n Peruana seasons}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Primera Division Peruana 1912}}\n[[Category:1912 in South American football leagues|Peru]]\n[[Category:Peruvian Primera Divisi\u00f3n seasons|1912]]\n[[Category:1912 in Peruvian football]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football league season\n  | competition        = [[Peruvian Primera Divisi\u00f3n]]\n  | season             = 1912\n  | winners            = [[Lima Cricket and Football Club|Lima Cricket]]<br>1st Primera Divisi\u00f3n title\n  | runners-up         = [[Ciclista Lima|Association]]\n  | relegated          = \n  | continentalcup1    = \n  | continentalcup1 qualifiers = \n  | continentalcup2    = \n  | continentalcup2 qualifiers = \n  | continentalcup3    = \n  | continentalcup3 qualifiers = \n  | league topscorer   = \n  | biggest home win   = \n  | biggest away win   = \n  | highest scoring    = \n  | total goals        = \n  | average goals      = \n  | longest wins       = \n  | longest unbeaten   = \n  | longest losses     = \n  | highest attendance = \n  | lowest attendance  = \n  | average attendance = \n  | prevseason         = \n  | nextseason         = [[1913 Liga Peruana de Football|1913]]\n}}\nThe '''1912 [[Peruvian Primera Divisi\u00f3n|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]]''' was the first season of top-flight Peruvian football. A total of 16 teams competed in the league, The champion was [[Lima Cricket and Football Club|Lima Cricket]]. This first season with organised league, covering [[Lima]], [[Callao]], and suburbs such as [[Miraflores District, Lima|Miraflores]] and [[Barranco District|Barranco]]. [[Sport Jos\u00e9 G\u00e1lvez|Jos\u00e9 G\u00e1lvez]] de Lima withdrew because of not agreeing with the competition format. The clubs from Callao (among which [[Atl\u00e9tico Chalaco]]) did not respond to the invitation to enter. The 16 teams were divided over a first and a second level, both of 8 clubs. Cricket and [[Ciclista Lima|Association]] finished equal on points; Cricket were declared champions on head-to-head record; Escuela Militar de Chorrillos withdrew halfway though the season when positioned last in the Primera Divisi\u00f3n with a single point. The first match was played on 5 May 1912 between Lima Cricket and Sport Vitarte. The match was a 6\u20131 win for Lima Cricket.\n\n==League table==\n===First Division===\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=QR\n|winpoints=2\n\n|team1=LCR|name_LCR=[[Lima Cricket and Football Club|Lima Cricket]]\n|team2=CIC|name_CIC=[[Ciclista Lima|Association]]\n|team3=JC1|name_JC1=[[Jorge Ch\u00e1vez No. 1|Jorge Ch\u00e1vez]]\n|team4=ALI|name_ALI=[[Alianza Lima|Sport Alianza]]\n|team5=MIR|name_MIR=[[Miraflores Sporting]]\n|team6=INC|name_INC=[[Sport Inca]]\n|team7=VIT|name_VIT=[[Sport Vitarte]]\n|team8=MCH|name_MCH=[[Escuela Militar de Chorrillos]]\n|win_LCR=1|draw_LCR=0|loss_LCR=0|gf_LCR=6|ga_LCR=1\n|win_CIC=0|draw_CIC=0|loss_CIC=1|gf_CIC=0|ga_CIC=1\n|win_JC1=1|draw_JC1=0|loss_JC1=0|gf_JC1=2|ga_JC1=0\n|win_ALI=0|draw_ALI=0|loss_ALI=1|gf_ALI=0|ga_ALI=2\n|win_MIR=2|draw_MIR=0|loss_MIR=0|gf_MIR=3|ga_MIR=0\n|win_INC=1|draw_INC=0|loss_INC=0|gf_INC=1|ga_INC=0\n|win_VIT=0|draw_VIT=0|loss_VIT=2|gf_VIT=1|ga_VIT=7\n|win_MCH=0|draw_MCH=0|loss_MCH=1|gf_MCH=0|ga_MCH=2\n|hth_LCR=LIMA 5\u20130 AFBC; AFBC 0\u20131 LIMA\n|hth_CIC=LCR\n|col_C=#ACE1AF|text_C=\n|result1=C\n|col_RET=inherit|text_RET=Retired\n|result8=RET\n\n|update=complete|source=\n}}\n\n==Title==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0 auto;\"\n|-\n!Liga Peruana de Football <br />1912 Champion\n|-\n|'''[[Lima Cricket and Football Club|Lima Cricket]]'''<br/>'''1st title '''\n|}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesp/peru1912.html Peru 1912 season] at [[RSSSF]]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110715174858/http://www.retrofutbolas.com/Templates/campeonatos.htm Peruvian Championship]\n*[http://sisbib.unmsm.edu.pe/bibVirtual/tesis/Human/Alvarez_E_T/Cap4.htm La Liga Peruana de Football]\n\n{{Primera Divisi\u00f3n Peruana seasons}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Primera Division Peruana 1912}}\n[[Category:1912 in South American football leagues|Peru]]\n[[Category:Peruvian Primera Divisi\u00f3n seasons|1912]]\n[[Category:1912 in Peruvian football]]\n", "name_user": "LilHelpa", 