{"title_page": "Yellow Second", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist  <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name                = Yellow Second\n| background          = group_or_band\n| origin              = [[Denver, Colorado|Denver]], [[Colorado]], [[United States|USA]]\n| genre               = [[power pop]]\n| years_active        = 1999-2005\n| label               = Floodgate Records<br/>Urban Achiever Records\n| associated_acts     = [[Five Iron Frenzy]], [[The Rocket Summer]]\n| current_members     = Scott Kerr<br/>Josh Hemingway<br/>Brett Bowden<br/>Sammy Sharon\n| past_members        = [[Andrew Verdecchio]]<br/>Joey Sanchez<br/>Matt Woll<br/>Nathan Marcy\n| website                 = [http://www.yellowsecond.com yellowsecond.com]\n}}\n\n'''Yellow Second''' was a melodic [[power pop]] band from [[Denver, Colorado]] formed in 1999 by Scott Kerr and [[Andrew Verdecchio]], both members of the [[ska]] band [[Five Iron Frenzy]].\n\nDuring their six-year stint, the band released three albums, ''June One'', ''Still Small'', and ''Altitude'' (See: [[Yellow Second#Discography|Discography]]). Additionally, several completed, though commercially unreleased tracks (referred to as \"B-sides\"), were made available for download on the band's official website. These tracks were entitled ''Waiting For No One, Velocity, Everything is Changing'', and ''Return Receipt Requested''. In late 2005, Yellow Second's disbandment was announced via the official [[Myspace]] account as well as the official website.\n\nScott Kerr, Yellow Second's foreman, claimed that his goal in the formation of the band was ''\"writing good songs which are musically interesting but also accessible\"''.<ref>[http://www.yourmusiczone.com/go/ymz/music_artist/yellow_second \"Yellow Second Biography @ YourMusicZone\"]</ref> Other themes include personal failings, romance, and allusions to the writing process.\n\nOn 22 June 2009, Yellow Second released the song \"Something to Do with You\" on MySpace.\n\n==Reunion==\n'''''Yellow Second''''' played a reunion show on May 9, 2008 at the Hi-Dive in [[Denver, Colorado]], performing alongside the musical acts '''''[[The Little Ones (band)|The Little Ones]]''''' and '''''Kissing Party'''''.\n\nIn \"The Rise and Fall of Five Iron Frenzy\" DVD released in 2010, Scott Kerr described Yellow Second as \"on-again, off-again,\" with no ambition of doing music for a living.\n\nIn 2011 [[John Warne]] of [[Relient K]] joined Yellow Second and they began work on a new album.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wilson|first=Shelby|title=Relient K - Interview|url=http://www.eastscene.com/2011/08/15/relient-k-warped-interview/|publisher=EastScene|accessdate=7 November 2011}}</ref> However, in late 2013 after joining the reunited Five Iron Frenzy, Kerr said that \"There isn\u2019t really a plan to do another [Yellow Second] record at this point.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Koestler|first=Larry|title=Interview with Scott Kerr of Five Iron Frenzy and Yellow Second|url=http://larrykoestler.com/2013/12/13/interview-with-scott-kerr-of-five-iron-frenzy-and-yellow-second/|publisher=larrykoestler.com/|accessdate=2 May 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n*''[[June One]]'' (2000)\n*''[[Still Small]]'' (November 2, 2002)\n*''[[Altitude (Yellow Second)|Altitude]]'' (March 8, 2005)\n\n==Current members==\n*Scott Kerr - [[Singing|vocals]], [[guitar]], keys\n*Josh Hemingway - [[guitar]]\n*Brett Bowden - [[bass guitar|bass]]\n*Sammy Sharon - [[Drum kit|drums]] (2005)\n\n==Past members==\n*Andy Verdecchio - [[Drum kit|drums]]\n*Joey Sanchez - [[Drum kit|drums]]\n*Matt Woll - [[bass guitar|bass]]\n*Nathan Marcy - [[bass guitar|bass]]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.purevolume.com/yellowsecond/ Yellow Second on purevolume]\n*[http://www.myspace.com/yellowsecond Yellow Second on MySpace]\n*[http://www.floodgaterecords.com/artistdetail/index.php?id=25 Yellow Second profile on Floodgate Records]\n*[http://www.floodgaterecords.com/ Floodgate Records]\n\n== Notes ==\n<references/>\n\n{{Five Iron Frenzy}}\n\n[[Category:Musical groups from Denver]]\n[[Category:American power pop groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 1999]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist  <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name                = Yellow Second\n| background          = group_or_band\n| origin              = [[Denver, Colorado|Denver]], [[Colorado]], [[United States|USA]]\n| genre               = [[power pop]]\n| years_active        = 1999-2005\n| label               = Floodgate Records<br/>Urban Achiever Records\n| associated_acts     = [[Five Iron Frenzy]], [[The Rocket Summer]]\n| current_members     = Scott Kerr<br/>Josh Hemingway<br/>Brett Bowden<br/>Sammy Sharon\n| past_members        = [[Andrew Verdecchio]]<br/>Joey Sanchez<br/>Matt Woll<br/>Nathan Marcy\n| website                 = [http://www.yellowsecond.com yellowsecond.com]\n}}\n\n'''Yellow Second''' was a melodic [[power pop]] band from [[Denver, Colorado]] formed in 1999 by Scott Kerr and [[Andrew Verdecchio]], both members of the [[ska]] band [[Five Iron Frenzy]].\n\nDuring their six-year stint, the band released three albums, ''June One'', ''Still Small'', and ''Altitude'' (See: [[Yellow Second#Discography|Discography]]). Additionally, several completed, though commercially unreleased tracks (referred to as \"B-sides\"), were made available for download on the band's official website. These tracks were entitled ''Waiting For No One, Velocity, Everything is Changing'', and ''Return Receipt Requested''. In late 2005, Yellow Second's disbandment was announced via the official [[Myspace]] account as well as the official website.\n\nScott Kerr, Yellow Second's foreman, claimed that his goal in the formation of the band was ''\"writing good songs which are musically interesting but also accessible\"''.<ref>[http://www.yourmusiczone.com/go/ymz/music_artist/yellow_second \"Yellow Second Biography @ YourMusicZone\"]</ref> Other themes include personal failings, romance, and allusions to the writing process.\n\nOn 22 June 2009, Yellow Second released the song \"Something to Do with You\" on MySpace.\n\n==Reunion==\n'''''Yellow Second''''' played a reunion show on May 9, 2008 at the Hi-Dive in [[Denver, Colorado]], performing alongside the musical acts '''''[[The Little Ones (band)|The Little Ones]]''''' and '''''Kissing Party'''''.\n\nAlso, according to a recent interview with drummer Andy Verdecchio, the band scheduled to play a show at Moe's Original Barbeque in [[Denver]], [[Colorado]].<ref>[http://fiveironfrenzy.com/?p=318]</ref>\n\nIn \"The Rise and Fall of Five Iron Frenzy\" DVD released in 2010, Scott Kerr described Yellow Second as \"on-again, off-again,\" with no ambition of doing music for a living.\n\nIn 2011 [[John Warne]] of [[Relient K]] joined Yellow Second and they began work on a new album.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wilson|first=Shelby|title=Relient K - Interview|url=http://www.eastscene.com/2011/08/15/relient-k-warped-interview/|publisher=EastScene|accessdate=7 November 2011}}</ref> However, in late 2013 after joining the reunited Five Iron Frenzy, Kerr said that \"There isn\u2019t really a plan to do another [Yellow Second] record at this point.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Koestler|first=Larry|title=Interview with Scott Kerr of Five Iron Frenzy and Yellow Second|url=http://larrykoestler.com/2013/12/13/interview-with-scott-kerr-of-five-iron-frenzy-and-yellow-second/|publisher=larrykoestler.com/|accessdate=2 May 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n*''[[June One]]'' (2000)\n*''[[Still Small]]'' (November 2, 2002)\n*''[[Altitude (Yellow Second)|Altitude]]'' (March 8, 2005)\n\n==Current members==\n*Scott Kerr - [[Singing|vocals]], [[guitar]], keys\n*Josh Hemingway - [[guitar]]\n*Brett Bowden - [[bass guitar|bass]]\n*Sammy Sharon - [[Drum kit|drums]] (2005)\n\n==Past members==\n*Andy Verdecchio - [[Drum kit|drums]]\n*Joey Sanchez - [[Drum kit|drums]]\n*Matt Woll - [[bass guitar|bass]]\n*Nathan Marcy - [[bass guitar|bass]]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.purevolume.com/yellowsecond/ Yellow Second on purevolume]\n*[http://www.myspace.com/yellowsecond Yellow Second on MySpace]\n*[http://www.floodgaterecords.com/artistdetail/index.php?id=25 Yellow Second profile on Floodgate Records]\n*[http://www.floodgaterecords.com/ Floodgate Records]\n\n== Notes ==\n<references/>\n\n{{Five Iron Frenzy}}\n\n[[Category:Musical groups from Denver]]\n[[Category:American power pop groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 1999]]\n", "name_user": "Coemgenv", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReunion", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yellow_Second"}
