{"title_page": "Mostafa Ronaghi", "text_new": "[[Image:Mostafa Ronaghi.jpg|thumb|right|Mostafa Ronaghi]]\n'''Mostafa Ronaghi''' ({{lang-fa|\u0645\u0635\u0637\u0641\u06cc \u0631\u0648\u0646\u0642\u06cc}}) (born 1968) is an [[Iran]]ian [[molecular biologist]], specializing in [[DNA sequencing]] methodology. He earned his Ph.D. from the [[Royal Institute of Technology]] in Sweden in 1998.\n\n{{As of|2008}}, he is the Chief Technology Officer and Senior Vice President at [[Illumina (company)|Illumina]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://investor.illumina.com/phoenix.zhtml?c=121127&p=irol-newsArticle&ID=1182777&highlight= |title=Illumina {{!}} 2008 Release: Illumina Appoints Mostafa Ronaghi as Senior Vice President and Chief Technology Officer |access-date=2008-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081003144414/http://investor.illumina.com/phoenix.zhtml?c=121127&p=irol-newsArticle&ID=1182777&highlight= |archive-date=2008-10-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Prior to this position, he was a principal investigator and Senior Research Associate at the [[Stanford Genome Technology Center]] at [[Stanford University]], focusing on developing analytical techniques for molecular diagnostics.\n\nHe is principal investigator for several grants including grants from the [[National Human Genome Research Institute]] (NHGRI), part of the [[National Institutes of Health]]<ref>[http://www.genome.gov/12513210 genome.gov | 2004 Release: NHGRI Seeks Next Generation of Sequencing Technologies<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> for the development of array-based [[Pyrosequencing]].\n\nIn 1998, he described together with [[P\u00e5l Nyr\u00e9n|P\u00e5l Nyren]] and [https://www.kth.se/en/bio/research/proteomics/proteomics-researchers/mathias-uhlen-1.67763 Mathias Uhlen]<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Ronaghi | first1 = M | last2 = Uhl\u00e9n | first2 = M | last3 = Nyr\u00e9n | first3 = P | year = 1998 | title = A sequencing method based on real-time pyrophosphate | url = | journal = Science | volume = 281 | issue = 5375| pages = 363\u2013365 | doi = 10.1126/science.281.5375.363 | pmid = 9705713 }}</ref> a solution-based variant of the [[pyrosequencing]] technology and co-founded '''Pyrosequencing AB''' (renamed to '''Biotage''' in 2003). He co-invented Molecular Inversion Probe assay and co-founded '''ParAllele BioScience''' to develop this multiplexed technology for genetic testing. ParAllele was acquired by [[Affymetrix]] in May 2005.\nIn 2005, he co-founded '''[[NextBio]]''', a search engine for life science data that was acquired by Illumina in 2013.<ref>[http://investor.illumina.com/phoenix.zhtml?ID=1869001&c=121127&highlight=&p=irol-newsArticle Illumina | Illumina Signs Agreement to Acquire NextBio, Leader in Analyzing and Aggregating Complex Genomic Data]</ref> He also serves on the board of directors of IntegenX and Aurora Biofuels. In 2008, Ronaghi and [[Helmy Eltoukhy]] co-founded '''[[Avantome]]''', a DNA sequencing company that was acquired by Illumina in July 2008.<ref>[http://www.tradingmarkets.com/.site/news/Stock%20News/1775391/ tradingmarkets.com | 2008 Release: Illumina To Acquire Privately-Held Avantome For $25 Million In Cash Upfront]{{Dead link|date=October 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"zz2\">{{cite web |url=https://www.fiercebiotech.com/biotech/illumina-snares-sequencing-tech-60m-buyout  |title=Illumina snares sequencing tech in $60M buyout |first=John |last=Carroll|date=23 Jul 2008 |website= fiercebiotech.com|publisher=Questex, LLC |access-date= 19 Oct 2019|quote=}}</ref>\n\n==Publications==\nAmong his approximately 50 peer-reviewed journal articles are the publications describing Pyrosequencing and Molecular Inversion Probe assays and other techniques:\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Absalan | first1 = F | last2 = Ronaghi | first2 = M | year = 2007 | title = Molecular inversion probe assay | url = | journal = [[Methods in Molecular Biology]] | volume = 396 | issue = | pages = 315\u201330 | doi = 10.1007/978-1-59745-515-2_20 | pmid = 18025701 }}\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Hardenbol | first1 = P | last2 = Ban\u00e9r | first2 = J | last3 = Jain | first3 = M | last4 = Nilsson | first4 = M | last5 = Namsaraev | first5 = EA | last6 = Karlin-Neumann | first6 = GA | last7 = Fakhrai-Rad | first7 = H | last8 = Ronaghi | first8 = M | last9 = Willis | first9 = TD | last10 = Landegren | first10 = U | last11 = Davis | first11 = RW | date = Jun 2003 | title = Multiplexed genotyping with sequence-tagged molecular inversion probes | url = | journal = [[Nature Biotechnology]] | volume = 21 | issue = 6| pages = 673\u20138 | doi = 10.1038/nbt821 | pmid = 12730666 }}\n* {{cite journal | date = Oct 2006 | title = Prediction of protein orientation upon immobilization on biological and nonbiological surfaces | url = | journal = [[Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences]] | volume = 103 | issue = 40| pages = 14773\u20138 | doi = 10.1073/pnas.0605841103 | pmid = 17001006 | pmc=1576295 | last1 = Talasaz | first1 = AH | last2 = Nemat-Gorgani | first2 = M | last3 = Liu | first3 = Y | display-authors = etal}}\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Ronaghi | first1 = M | date = Jan 2001 | title = Pyrosequencing sheds light on DNA sequencing | url = | journal = [[Genome Research]] | volume = 11 | issue = 1| pages = 3\u201311 | doi = 10.1101/gr.11.1.3 | pmid = 11156611 }}\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Ronaghi | first1 = M | last2 = Uhl\u00e9n | first2 = M | last3 = Nyr\u00e9n | first3 = P | date = Jul 1998 | title = A sequencing method based on real-time pyrophosphate | url = | journal = [[Science (journal)|Science]] | volume = 281 | issue = 5375| pages = 363\u2013365 | doi = 10.1126/science.281.5375.363 | pmid = 9705713 }}\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Ronaghi | first1 = M | last2 = Karamohamed | first2 = S | last3 = Pettersson | first3 = B | last4 = Uhl\u00e9n | first4 = M | last5 = Nyr\u00e9n | first5 = P | date = Nov 1996 | title = Real-time DNA sequencing using detection of pyrophosphate release | url = | journal = [[Analytical Biochemistry]] | volume = 242 | issue = 1| pages = 84\u20139 | doi = 10.1006/abio.1996.0432 | pmid = 8923969 }}\n\nHe also holds about 20 patents.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n*[Pyrosequencing Array for DNA Sequencing]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://med.stanford.edu/sgtc/general/staff.html Stanford Genome Technology Center]\n* [http://www.nextbio.com NextBio]\n* [http://www.integenx.com IntegenX, Inc.]\n* [http://www.aurorabiofuels.com Aurora Biofuels]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ronaghi, Mostafa}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:KTH Royal Institute of Technology alumni]]\n[[Category:American people of Iranian descent]]\n[[Category:Iranian biologists]]\n[[Category:Iranian academics]]\n[[Category:Iranian chief technology officers]]\n", "text_old": "[[Image:Mostafa Ronaghi.jpg|thumb|right|Mostafa Ronaghi]]\n'''Mostafa Ronaghi''' ({{lang-fa|\u0645\u0635\u0637\u0641\u06cc \u0631\u0648\u0646\u0642\u06cc}}) (born 1968) is an [[Iran]]ian [[molecular biologist]], specializing in [[DNA sequencing]] methodology. He earned his Ph.D. from the [[Royal Institute of Technology]] in Sweden in 1998.\n\n{{As of|2008}}, he is the Chief Technology Officer and Senior Vice President at [[Illumina (company)|Illumina]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://investor.illumina.com/phoenix.zhtml?c=121127&p=irol-newsArticle&ID=1182777&highlight= |title=Illumina {{!}} 2008 Release: Illumina Appoints Mostafa Ronaghi as Senior Vice President and Chief Technology Officer |access-date=2008-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081003144414/http://investor.illumina.com/phoenix.zhtml?c=121127&p=irol-newsArticle&ID=1182777&highlight= |archive-date=2008-10-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Prior to this position, he was a principal investigator and Senior Research Associate at the [[Stanford Genome Technology Center]] at [[Stanford University]], focusing on developing analytical techniques for molecular diagnostics.\n\nHe is principal investigator for several grants including grants from the [[National Human Genome Research Institute]] (NHGRI), part of the [[National Institutes of Health]]<ref>[http://www.genome.gov/12513210 genome.gov | 2004 Release: NHGRI Seeks Next Generation of Sequencing Technologies<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> for the development of array-based [[Pyrosequencing]].\n\nIn 1998, he described together with [[P\u00e5l Nyr\u00e9n|P\u00e5l Nyren]] and [https://www.kth.se/en/bio/research/proteomics/proteomics-researchers/mathias-uhlen-1.67763 Mathias Uhlen]<ref>Ronaghi, M; Uhl\u00e9n, M; Nyr\u00e9n, P (Jul 1998). \"A sequencing method based on real-time pyrophosphate\". Science. 281 (5375): 363\u2013365. {{PMID|9705713}}. doi:10.1126/science.281.5375.363</ref> a solution-based variant of the [[pyrosequencing]] technology and co-founded '''Pyrosequencing AB''' (renamed to '''Biotage''' in 2003). He co-invented Molecular Inversion Probe assay and co-founded '''ParAllele BioScience''' to develop this multiplexed technology for genetic testing. ParAllele was acquired by [[Affymetrix]] in May 2005.\nIn 2005, he co-founded '''[[NextBio]]''', a search engine for life science data that was acquired by Illumina in 2013.<ref>[http://investor.illumina.com/phoenix.zhtml?ID=1869001&c=121127&highlight=&p=irol-newsArticle Illumina | Illumina Signs Agreement to Acquire NextBio, Leader in Analyzing and Aggregating Complex Genomic Data]</ref> He also serves on the board of directors of IntegenX and Aurora Biofuels. In 2008, Ronaghi and [[Helmy Eltoukhy]] co-founded '''[[Avantome]]''', a DNA sequencing company that was acquired by Illumina in July 2008.<ref>[http://www.tradingmarkets.com/.site/news/Stock%20News/1775391/ tradingmarkets.com | 2008 Release: Illumina To Acquire Privately-Held Avantome For $25 Million In Cash Upfront]{{Dead link|date=October 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"zz2\"> {{cite web |url=https://www.fiercebiotech.com/biotech/illumina-snares-sequencing-tech-60m-buyout  |title=Illumina snares sequencing tech in $60M buyout |first=John |last=Carroll|date=23 Jul 2008 |website= fiercebiotech.com|publisher=Questex, LLC |access-date= 19 Oct 2019|quote=}}</ref>\n\n==Publications==\nAmong his approximately 50 peer-reviewed journal articles are the publications describing Pyrosequencing and Molecular Inversion Probe assays and other techniques:\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Absalan | first1 = F | last2 = Ronaghi | first2 = M | year = 2007 | title = Molecular inversion probe assay | url = | journal = [[Methods in Molecular Biology]] | volume = 396 | issue = | pages = 315\u201330 | doi = 10.1007/978-1-59745-515-2_20 | pmid = 18025701 }}\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Hardenbol | first1 = P | last2 = Ban\u00e9r | first2 = J | last3 = Jain | first3 = M | last4 = Nilsson | first4 = M | last5 = Namsaraev | first5 = EA | last6 = Karlin-Neumann | first6 = GA | last7 = Fakhrai-Rad | first7 = H | last8 = Ronaghi | first8 = M | last9 = Willis | first9 = TD | last10 = Landegren | first10 = U | last11 = Davis | first11 = RW | date = Jun 2003 | title = Multiplexed genotyping with sequence-tagged molecular inversion probes | url = | journal = [[Nature Biotechnology]] | volume = 21 | issue = 6| pages = 673\u20138 | doi = 10.1038/nbt821 | pmid = 12730666 }}\n* {{cite journal | date = Oct 2006 | title = Prediction of protein orientation upon immobilization on biological and nonbiological surfaces | url = | journal = [[Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences]] | volume = 103 | issue = 40| pages = 14773\u20138 | doi = 10.1073/pnas.0605841103 | pmid = 17001006 | pmc=1576295}}\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Ronaghi | first1 = M | date = Jan 2001 | title = Pyrosequencing sheds light on DNA sequencing | url = | journal = [[Genome Research]] | volume = 11 | issue = 1| pages = 3\u201311 | doi = 10.1101/gr.11.1.3 | pmid = 11156611 }}\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Ronaghi | first1 = M | last2 = Uhl\u00e9n | first2 = M | last3 = Nyr\u00e9n | first3 = P | date = Jul 1998 | title = A sequencing method based on rea