te=17 December 2016|title=Not Even a Prosperous Slovakia Is Immune to Doubts About the E.U.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/17/world/europe/slovakia-european-union-populists-migrants.html}}</ref>\n* [[Christian fundamentalism]]<ref name=\"Exit poll: Kres\u0165anstvo a trad\u00edcie\"/>\n* [[National conservatism]]<ref name=\"Exit poll: Kres\u0165anstvo a trad\u00edcie\"/>\n* [[Social conservatism]]<ref name=\"Exit poll: Kres\u0165anstvo a trad\u00edcie\"/>\n* [[Tradition]]alism<ref name=\"Exit poll: Kres\u0165anstvo a trad\u00edcie\"/>\n* [[Anti-globalization movement|Anti-globalism]]<ref>{{cite web|language=sk|title=Totalita pod r\u00fa\u0161kom demokracie|url=http://www.naseslovensko.net/nase-nazory/totalita-pod-ruskom-demokracie/|website=naseslovensko.net|date=30 September 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Euroscepticism#Hard Euroscepticism|Hard Euroscepticism]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://euobserver.com/beyond-brussels/132562|title=Slovakia vote shocks Europe and its own society|access-date=2017-02-14|date=2016-03-07}}</ref>\n* [[Russophilia]]<ref name=\"aktuality\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.aktuality.sk/clanok/526205/naka-preverovala-kotlebu-kvoli-peniazom-z-ruska/|title=NAKA veriffied Kotleba because of money from Russia|access-date=2017-03-10|date=2017-03-10}}</ref>}}\n| headquarters = [[Bansk\u00e1 Bystrica]]\n| international = \n| website = {{URL|http://www.naseslovensko.net/}}\n| country = Slovakia\n| membership_year = 2018\n| membership = 1439<ref>{{cite web|title=Najviac stran\u00edkov si suver\u00e9nne dr\u017e\u00ed Smer-SD, nasleduj\u00fa SMK a KDH\n|url=https://www.hlavnespravy.sk/najviac-stranikov-si-suverenne-drzi-smer-sd-nasleduju-smk-kdh/1502196|website=hlavnespravy.sk|accessdate=25 August 2018|date=2018-08-25}}</ref>\n| newspaper = ''Na\u0161e Slovensko''<br />(''Our Slovakia'')\n| native_name = Kotlebovci \u2013 \u013dudov\u00e1 strana Na\u0161e Slovensko\n| position = [[Far-right politics|Far-right]]<ref name=\"Klapsis2015\">{{cite book|author=Antonis Klapsis|title=An Unholy Alliance: The European Far Right and Putin's Russia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=va6rCQAAQBAJ&pg=PA14|year=2015|publisher=Wilfried Martens Centre for European Studies|isbn=978-2-930632-39-1|page=14}}</ref>\n| european = [[Alliance for Peace and Freedom]]\n| europarl = [[Non-Inscrits]]\n| colours = {{Color box|{{Kotleba \u2013 People's Party Our Slovakia/meta/color}}|border=darkgray}} Green\n| slogan = ''S odvahou proti syst\u00e9mu''<br />(\"With Courage Against the System\")\n| anthem = \"[[Hej, Slov\u00e1ci]]\"<br />(\"Hey, Slovaks\")<ref>{{cite web|title=spev\u00e1cky zbor z Brezna zaspievan\u00edm hymny prv\u00e9ho slovensk\u00e9ho \u0161t\u00e1tu Hej, Slov\u00e1ci. V tej chv\u00edli bola u\u017e cel\u00e1 s\u00e1la na noh\u00e1ch a v\u0161etci pr\u00edtomn\u00ed spievali t\u00fato n\u00e1dhern\u00fa piese\u0148, ktor\u00e1 je z\u00e1rove\u0148 aj hymnou \u013dudovej strany Na\u0161e Slovensko|url=https://dennikn.sk/1634639/lsns-je-neonacisticka-strana-usvedcuju-ju-jej-spojenci-aj-vlastne-ciny/|website=dennikn.sk|accessdate=31 October 2019|date=2019-10-31}}</ref>\n| seats1_title = [[National Council of the Slovak Republic|National Council]]\n| seats1 = {{Composition bar|17|150|hex={{Kotleba \u2013 People's Party Our Slovakia/meta/color}}}}\n| seats2_title = [[European Parliament]]\n| seats2 = {{Composition bar|2|14|hex={{Kotleba \u2013 People's Party Our Slovakia/meta/color}}}}\n| seats3_title = [[Regions of Slovakia|Presidents of self-governing regions]]\n| seats3 = {{Composition bar|0|8|{{Kotleba \u2013 People's Party Our Slovakia/meta/color}}}}\n| seats4_title = [[Regions of Slovakia|Regional parliaments]]\n| seats4 = {{Composition bar|2|408| {{Kotleba \u2013 People's Party Our Slovakia/meta/color}}}}\n| seats5_title = Local councils\n| seats5 = {{Composition bar|42|20646|{{Kotleba \u2013 People's Party Our Slovakia/meta/color}}}}\n| flag = Kotleba-\u013dSNS New Flag.png\n}}\nThe '''People's Party \u2013 Our Slovakia''' ({{lang-sk|\u013dudov\u00e1 strana \u2013 Na\u0161e Slovensko}}, \u013dSNS), formerly known as '''Kotleba \u2013 People's Party Our Slovakia''', and since November 2019 officially known as '''Kotlebists \u2013 People's Party Our Slovakia''' ({{lang-sk|Kotlebovci \u2013 \u013dudov\u00e1 strana Na\u0161e Slovensko|links=no}}), is a [[Far-right politics|far-right]] [[Neo-Nazism|neo-Nazi]]<ref name=\"auto1\"/><ref name=\"cbsnews.com\"/><ref name=\"politico.eu\"/> [[List of political parties in Slovakia|political party]] in [[Slovakia]].<ref name=\"Vicenova13\">{{Cite news |first=Radka |last=Vicenov\u00e1 |title=Slovakia: right-wing extremism on the rise |work=openDemocracy |date=19 December 2013 |url=https://www.opendemocracy.net/can-europe-make-it/radka-vicenov%C3%A1/slovakia-right-wing-extremism-on-rise}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |first1=Miroslav |last1=Mare\u0161 |first2=Richard |last2=Stojar |title=Extreme right perpetrators |work=Understanding Lone Actor Terrorism: Past experience, future outlook, and response strategies |publisher=Routledge |year=2016 |page=80}}</ref><ref name=\"Nociar12_5s\">{{Cite journal|last=Nociar|first=Tom\u00e1\u0161|date=December 2012|title=Right-Wing Extremism in Slovakia|url=http://library.fes.de/pdf-files/id-moe/09567.pdf|pages=5\u20136|journal=Friedrich-Ebert-Stiftung International Policy Analysis}}</ref><ref name=\"Pytlas2015\">{{cite book|author=Bartek Pytlas|title=Radical Right Parties in Central and Eastern Europe: Mainstream Party Competition and Electoral Fortune|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FOC9CgAAQBAJ&pg=PA224|year=2015|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-317-49586-4|page=224}}</ref> The party derives its origin from the legacy of [[\u013dudov\u00edt \u0160t\u00far]], [[Andrej Hlinka]] and [[Jozef Tiso]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.naseslovensko.net/o-nas/|title=O n\u00e1s|newspaper=Kotleba - \u013dudov\u00e1 strana Na\u0161e Slovensko|access-date=2017-02-14|language=sk-SK}}</ref>\n{{Neo-Fascism}}\n\nPositioned on the far-right of the political spectrum, Kotlebists \u2013 People's Party Our Slovakia's political platform expresses [[xenophobic]] and [[Anti-ziganism|antiziganist]] rhetoric,<ref name=\"Nociar12_5s\" /> Christian fundamentalism, paternalism and economic interventionism, interest-free national loans, replacement of the [[euro]] currency with the [[Slovak koruna]], strengthening of law and order, rejection of same-sex [[civil unions]] and LGBT rights, and strong anti-establishment sentiment, most notably against Slovakia's current foreign and domestic policy.\n\nThe party proposes to reduce the number of MPs from 150 to 100, restrict the expression of \"degenerate material\" in media, establish a home guard militia with the goal of cracking down on \"gypsy criminality\", promoting a mixed economy, prohibiting abortion conducted in the second and third trimester, institute a national health service, subsidizing families in accordance to their fertility, and to withdraw the Slovak military from foreign operations. In addition, it advocates for Slovakia's departure from the [[European Union]], the [[European Monetary Union]], and [[NATO]], and advocates for closer ties with the [[Russian Federation]] and the [[CSTO]].<ref name=\"Nociar12_5s\"/>\n\n== History ==\nThe origins of the party are closely related to the nationalist [[Slovak Brotherhood|Slovak Togetherness]] organization.<ref>{{Cite journal |first=Tom\u00e1\u0161 |last=Nociar |title=Right-Wing Extremism in Slovakia |journal=Friedrich-Ebert-Stiftung International Policy Analysis |date=December 2012 |pages=4}}</ref> The members of the movement tried to run in the 2006 elections under the name Slovak Togetherness \u2013 National Party, which was forcibly dissolved by the Supreme Court on grounds of anti-constitutional and anti-democratic activities.<ref name=\"Perex\">{{cite web |url=http://spravy.pravda.sk/domace/clanok/150013-najvyssi-sud-rozpustil-slovensku-pospolitost |title= Najvy\u0161\u0161\u00ed s\u00fad rozpustil Slovensk\u00fa pospolitos\u0165| trans-title = The Supreme Court dissolved Slovak Togetherness | website=Pravda |publisher=Perex |date=1 March 2006 |access-date=7 March 2016 |language=Slovak}}</ref> Instead of founding an entirely new party, former members of Slovak Togetherness under the leadership of [[Marian Kotleba]] [[Entryism|hijacked]] the tiny Party of the Friends of Wine that had existed since 2000, changed its name to People's Party of Social Solidarity in May 2009, and then finally altered it to People's Party \u2013 Our Slovakia in early 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ives.sk/registre/detailuplnyps.do?action=uplny&formular=&id=153101 |title=Register of Political Parties and Political Movements |website=Organization for Information Technologies of Public Administration |publisher=Ministry of Interior of the Slovak Republic |access-date=7 March 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160412081315/http://www.ives.sk/registre/detailuplnyps.do?action=uplny&formular=&id=153101 |archive-date=12 April 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> This was done to avoid the legal difficulties with registering a new party under this name given that a different party called Our Slovakia already existed.<ref name=\"Nociar12_5s\"/>\n\nDuring the elections of 2016, the party nominated several controversial and extremist candidates, such as an ex-singer of [[Neo-Nazism|neo-Nazi]] music bands [[Kr\u00e1tky proces]] and Juden Mord and a candidate who openly admired [[Adolf Hitler]] and promoted Hlinka's historical clericofascist [[Slovak People's Party]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hnonline.sk/slovensko/592397-fanusik-hitlera-ci-spevak-juden-mordu-aj-tito-kandiduju-do-parlamentu|title=Fan\u00fa\u0161ik Hitlera \u010di spev\u00e1k Juden Mordu, aj t\u00edto kandiduj\u00fa do parlamentu|trans-title=A fan of Hitler and a singer of Juden Mord - even these candidates are running for Parliament|website=HN Online|publisher=MAFRA Slovakia, a.s.|date=17 February 2016|access-date=7 March 2016|language=Slovak|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170728155449/http://hnonline.sk/slovensko/592397-fanusik-hitlera-ci-spevak-juden-mordu-aj-tito-kandiduju-do-parlamentu|archive-date=28 July 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Ties to fascism and far-right extremism ==\nThe party is classified by politicians, academics, media outlets, and political scientists as being [[Fascism|fascist]] in nature. This is due to some members of the party being connected to extremist movements such as the [[Slovak Brotherhood]] in Kotleba's case or the fact the party and its members requested a minute of silence for [[Jozef Tiso]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tellmamauk.org/tag/marian-kotleba/|title=Marian Kotleba Archives - TELL MAMA|website=TELL MAMA|access-date=2017-02-14}}</ref> who instituted a clericofascist dictatorship, supported and actively put laws in place during the [[Second World War]] that discriminated against Jews, and made the country pay [[Nazi Germany]] to deport Slovak Jews during [[the Holocaust in Slovakia]].<ref>{{cite book |last1=Ward |first1=James Mace |title=Priest, Politician, Collaborator: Jozef Tiso and the Making of Fascist Slovakia |date=2013|location=Ithaka |publisher=Cornell University Press |isbn=978-0-8014-6812-4 |language=en |ref=harv}}</ref> Kotleba formerly dressed in a uniform resembling the [[Hlinka Guard]], described Jews as \"devils in human skin\", and promoted the conspiracy theory of a [[Zionist Occupation Government]]. The party distanced itself from its nostalgia for the Slovak State following failure during the 2006 elections, and instead focused on anti-Roma comments.<ref>{{cite journal |first=Nina |last1=Paulovi\u010dov\u00e1 |title=Holocaust Memory and Antisemitism in Slovakia: The Postwar Era to the Present |journal=[[Antisemitism Studies]]|publisher=Indiana University Press |date=2018 |volume=2 |issue=1 |pages=17, 19\u201322|doi=10.2979/antistud.2.1.02|ref=harv|quote=On March 14, 2004, in his public speech to commemorate the establishment of the 1939 Slovak state, Marian Kotleba, the leader of the extreme PP-OS (People\u2019s Party Our Slovakia), mocked efforts to come to terms with the Holocaust past and marked out Jews as \u201cdevils in human skin.\u201d Kotleba further promoted the view of \u013dudov\u00edt \u0160t\u00far\u2014the leading representative of Slovak national revival in the nineteenth century\u2014that Jews have no historical, cultural, or social ties with Slovaks. When the Jewish community expressed outrage against the demonstration of Kotleba supporters in Kom\u00e1rno in 2005, Kotleba defended the extremists by accusing Jews of plotting \u201cagainst the Slovak nation, statehood, and Christian traditions\u201d often with the help of the \u201cMagyar chauvinists and domestic traitors.\u201d In Kotleba\u2019s eyes, every political skirmish in Slovakia is a \u201cvery well prepared performance\u201d directed by Z. O. G. (the \u201cZionist Occupation Government\u201d).}}</ref>  Kotleba and his party was also described by both the Slovak President [[Andrej Kiska]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://spectator.sme.sk/c/20133813/kiska-lets-be-clear-kotleba-is-fascist.html|title=Kiska: Let's be clear, Kotleba is fascist|last=a.s.|first=Petit Press|newspaper=spectator.sme.sk|access-date=2017-02-14}}</ref> and Czech President [[Milo\u0161 Zeman]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.novinky.cz/domaci/396911-zeman-kotlebova-lidova-strana-je-fasisticka.html|title=Zeman: Kotlebova Lidov\u00e1 strana je fa\u0161istick\u00e1|newspaper=Novinky.cz|access-date=2017-02-14|language=cs-CZ}}</ref> as fascist. The party officially denies any connection to fascism and perceives the accusations as unfounded hoaxes.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.naseslovensko.net/tlacove-konferencie/tlacova-konferencia-vznik-politickej-policie-povazujeme-za-prejav-fasizmu-vladnej-moci/|title=Tla\u010dov\u00e1 konferencia: Vznik politickej pol\u00edcie pova\u017eujeme za prejav fa\u0161izmu vl\u00e1dnej moci|newspaper=Kotleba - \u013dudov\u00e1 strana Na\u0161e Slovensko|access-date=2017-02-14|language=sk-SK}}</ref>\n\nMembers of the party have been repeatedly charged with [[Holocaust denial]], which is a felony in Slovakia.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mazurek not prosecuted for Holocaust denial |url=https://spectator.sme.sk/c/20266405/mazurek-not-prosecuted-for-holocaust-denial.html |accessdate=16 January 2019 |work=The Slovak Spectator |date=7 September 2016 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Extremist charged with Holocaust denial |url=https://spectator.sme.sk/c/20617009/extremist-charged-with-holocaust-denial.html |accessdate=16 January 2019 |work=The Slovak Spectator |date=2 August 2017 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2017, the General Prosecutor's Office of the Slovak Republic made a notice to the Supreme Court, requesting the dissolution of the party.  The General Prosecutor's Office reasoned this step by pointing to the pro-fascist tendencies of the party, violation of the constitution of the Slovak Republic and violation of Slovak and international laws.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://spravy.pravda.sk/domace/clanok/430584-ciznar-dal-navrh-na-rozpustenie-kotlebovej-strany/|title=\u010ci\u017en\u00e1r dal n\u00e1vrh na rozpustenie Kotlebovej strany|website=Pravda|language=Slovak|access-date=2017-05-17}}</ref>\n\nDuring the party's congress meeting on 29 March, 2018, a new logo was proposed which replaced the old logo depicting a straight Slovak double-cross which bore a strong resemblance to the logo  used by [[Hlinka's Slovak People's Party|HS\u013dS]] and the [[Hlinka Guard]] during the [[Slovak State|First Slovak Republic]] with the new logo that depicts the classic Slovak double-cross standing atop the [[Tatra Mountains]]. The party claimed that they changed the logo to distance themselves from fascism, Nazism, or any form of rightwing extremism.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.naseslovensko.net/nasa-praca/zo-zakulisia-ls-nase-slovensko-zaznam-z-celostatneho-snemu-predstavenie-noveho-loga-strany/|title=Zo z\u00e1kulisia \u013dS Na\u0161e Slovensko: Z\u00e1znam z celo\u0161t\u00e1tneho snemu, predstavenie nov\u00e9ho loga strany|website=naseslovensko.sk|language=Slovak|access-date=2017-03-29}}</ref> As of 2020, the party spokesperson was Ondrej Durica, a former member of the neo-Nazi band ''Biely Odpor'' (White Resistance). 2020 candidate Andrej Medvecky was convicted of attacking a black man while shouting racial slurs; another candidate, Anton Gr\u0148o, was fined for making a [[Na str\u00e1\u017e|fascist salute]]. The party still celebrates 14 March, the anniversary of the founding of the Slovak State.<ref name=fp>{{cite news |last1=Colborne |first1=Michael |title=Marian Kotleba Wants to Make Slovakia Fascist Again |url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/02/28/marian-kotleba-slovakia-election-right-wing-fascism/ |accessdate=15 March 2020 |work=Foreign Policy |date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Program and manifesto ==\n{{multiple image|| direction         = vertical\n|image1=Flag of the Hlinka party (1938\u20131945) variant 2.svg\n|image2=Flag-KLSNS.svg\n|image3=Kotleba-\u013dSNS New Flag.png\n|footer=From top: [[Hlinka's Slovak People's Party]] flag, Kotleba's former flag, Kotleba's current flag}}\nIn the manifesto of Kotleba \u2013 People's Party Our Slovakia, the party states it wants a \"functioning state\" that is free from corruption, foreign influences and \"larceny of public finance\". It seeks to give the general public the power to  recall any member of the parliament and it wishes to decrease the total number of seats within the National Council from 150 to 100. Additionally, it wants to introduce a flat tax rate of 15% and stop the financing of campaigns for political parties from the state budget.<ref name=\"naseslovensko.net\">{{cite web |url=http://www.naseslovensko.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Volebn%C3%BD-program-2016.pdf |title=Program |website=www.naseslovensko.net}}</ref>\n\nThe party sees the [[EU]] and [[NATO]] as \"undermining the sovereignty of the Slovak nation\", and wants to leave these organizations in order to \"give Slovakia complete [[sovereignty]] and not be part of [[United States war crimes|American war crimes]] and a toy in the hands of foreign superpowers\". \u013dSNS also advocates the investigation of foreign [[NGOs]] for possible corruption or unlawful activity, forcing opposition news outlets to be classified as \"foreign agents\", and to \"liberate Slovakia from the slavery of foreign bankers\".<ref name=\"naseslovensko.net\"/>\n\nAs for internal security, the party wants to establish a home guard with the intention of protecting the people in areas  where legitimate police forces are not adequate at stopping \"Gypsy extremists\" who \"steal, rape and murder\" the \"decent people\", while also advocating the arming of the populace for the protection of personal life and private property. The party also wants to make politicians responsible for any criminal or corrupt activity they partake in while being a public servant and to be punished accordingly. In addition, \u013dSNS also intends to make police forces undergo training in illegal settlements inhabited by the resident Romani populace and demolish any illegal structures, whether they are \"black settlements\" or \"palaces of the rich\". The party seeks to re-establish border control on each segment of the country's borders and give the parliament the ability to use the army to secure and patrol these borders if necessary.<ref name=\"naseslovensko.net\"/>\n\nDue to the country's armed forces being small and ill-prepared as a result of conscription being abolished, \u013dSNS sees it as necessary to modernize, renew, and increase the size of the Slovak Armed Forces to be able to \"effectively protect the nation from any foreign threats when it leaves NATO\", to prevent the \"hordes of Muslim immigrants\" from coming to Slovakia, and to protect [[Christianity]] and [[Culture of Europe|European culture]] from \"Islamization\".<ref name=\"naseslovensko.net\"/>\n\nThe party plans to give jobs to the long-term unemployed through public works programmes. These jobs would consist of the maintenance of roads, schools, national memorials, hospitals and construction of housing as part of their social policy. The retirement age would be lowered to 60 years and the government would increase financial benefits for mothers with children, with rentable housing being provided to \"law-abiding and decent families\" and benefits to \"non-working gypsy thieves\" and \"asocials\" being cancelled.<ref name=\"naseslovensko.net\"/>\n\nThe party also seeks to nationalize the health care system in order to provide universal comprehensive healthcare for the citizens of Slovakia, as written in the Constitution of Slovakia, and to create one national health insurance organization. Additionally, the party wants to return to a centralized emergency service and to make sure that every ambulance has a physician on board to administer appropriate medical care. Furthermore, the party wants to indoctrinate children with traditionalist and fundamentalist Christian values, to \"protect them from violent media\", and to ban the operation of gambling machines in the country, while supporting and subsidizing domestic culture and artists to prevent Slovakia from \"descending into a degenerate society made up by [[consumerism]], [[secularism]] and empty [[liberalism]]\".<ref name=\"naseslovensko.net\"/>\n\nThe party also seeks to subsidize tertiary education through taxes and eliminate college tuition, effectively introducing free college in Slovakia. In regards to the banking sector, the party intends to nationalize all private banks in the country  and create one state-run central bank under the control of the government. The party also wants to nationalize all strategic industries of the country, such as powerplants, steel and automobile manufacturing, mining, agriculture, railways, or public transport. The party wants to assure energy and food self-sufficiency to make the country less dependent on imports, by rebuilding the agricultural industry and placing a strong emphasis on locally produced goods. In addition, the party seeks to get rid of bureaucracy and red tape in business to increase growth of domestic companies.<ref name=\"naseslovensko.net\"/>\n\nThe party rejects the [[Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership|TTIP agreement]], advocates a departure from the [[European Monetary Union]], and seeks to re-establish the previous currency, the [[Slovak koruna]], in order to give the state and the central bank authority to decide on the country's monetary policy. Moreover, the party advocates for the protection of the environment from pollution and exploitation by implementing conservationist laws and regulation and supporting the research and development of [[renewable energy]].<ref name=\"naseslovensko.net\"/>\n\n\u013dSNS has also made proposals in parliament for the banning of abortion conducted in the second and third trimester and contraception in Slovakia, and is staunchly opposed to LGBT rights, denouncing the LGBT community as freaks and perverts and pushing for an active crackdown on homosexual activists and media, and the party also supports a constitutional ban on LGBT partnerships.<ref name=\"naseslovensko.net\"/>\n\nThe party is vocally opposed to liberalism and [[Atlanticism]], and harbours strong anti-establishment sentiment, rejecting the standard left-right classification and positions itself as a [[Syncretism|syncretic]] movement. Other policies include opposition to gun control, rejection of same-sex marriages, banning abortions conducted after the third month of pregnancy, withholding of welfare funds for those who refuse to work, ending the financing of NGOs and protesting NATO convoys going through Slovakia. In 2019, the party resumed its notorious campaign to collect enough petition signatures to leave the North Atlantic Treaty Organization.<ref name=\"naseslovensko.net\"/>\n\n== Views on Roma and migrants ==\nThe party sees and describes the unintegrated groups of [[Romani people]] as being a drain on the social security system due to large Roma families receiving a higher amount of benefits for children compared to ethnic Slovaks. This especially applies to illegal Roma settlements, where these \"gypsy extremists\", as the party calls them, often reside in. Occasionally, the party has said that it wants to crackdown on \"Gypsy terror\" and uses the [[Kr\u00e1sna H\u00f4rka Castle]] fire of 2012 as an example of \"gypsy criminality\", whilst using rhetoric that describes the \"gypsy extremists\" as \"social parasites\" and \"extremists that steal, rape and murder decent people\".<ref name=\"naseslovensko.net\"/>\n\nAccording to the party, immigrants from third world countries are \"invaders who are supported by [[globalists]] to destroy the old continent of Europe\". The party is against the acceptance of even a single refugee, stating that \"even one is too much\", while blaming the EU and the [[Schengen Agreement]] for alleged \"immigrant invasion\".<ref name=\"naseslovensko.net\"/>\n\n== Pro-Russian activities==\n[[File:STOP_NATO.JPG|right|thumb|An anti-NATO and anti-American sign that was hung on the governor's building during Kotleba's rule in 2014.]]\nMarian Kotleba, during his governorship of the [[Bansk\u00e1 Bystrica region]], sent a personal letter on January 31, 2014 to [[Viktor Yanukovych]] during the [[Euromaidan|Euromaidan revolution]] in Ukraine, urging him as a \"fellow Slav\" not to \"surrender his country to EU interests, markets and NATO aggression, to stay vigilant against foreign coup d'etats, and to remember what happened to Serbian national heroes such as [[Slobodan Milo\u0161evi\u0107]]\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.topky.sk/cl/100535/1376595/Kotleba-napisal-Janukovycovi-otvoreny-list|title=Kotleba nap\u00edsal Janukovy\u010dovi otvoren\u00fd list|newspaper=Topky.sk|access-date=2017-02-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170805221013/http://www.topky.sk/cl/100535/1376595/Kotleba-napisal-Janukovycovi-otvoreny-list|archive-date=2017-08-05|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nOn August 29, 2014, Marian Kotleba hung up a sign saying \"Yankees go home! STOP NATO!\" on the governor's building in [[Bansk\u00e1 Bystrica]], demonstrating the party's [[anti-Americanism]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.webnoviny.sk/slovensko/clanok/861436-marian-kotleba-vyvesil-na-urad-vlajku-s-napisom-stop-nato/|title=Kotleba dal na \u00farad transparent Yankees go home! Stop NATO!|last=Webnoviny.sk|newspaper=Webnoviny.sk}}</ref>\n\nOn May 5, 2016, the \u013dSNS branch located in the Bansk\u00e1 Bystrica region hung up a Russian flag in the city of [[Bansk\u00e1 Bystrica]], to show solidarity with the Russian community in the city and the [[Night Wolves]] biker club.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pluska.sk/plus-7-dni/domov/kotleba-zase-predviedol-urad-bbsk-zavesil-rusku-vlajku.html|title=Kotleba sa zase predviedol: Na \u00darad BBSK zavesil rusk\u00fa vlajku, je to \u0165ah na voli\u010dov?|newspaper=www.pluska.sk}}</ref> which came to commemorate the Russian victory over fascism. The party also sent 3 people, including 1 MP, to commemorate the [[Slovak National Uprising]] at the SNP monument and museum. However, party leader Marian Kotleba denounced the Allied campaign during the Uprising and indirectly endorsed the pro-Axis [[Slovak Republic (1939\u20131945)|Slovak State]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://spravy.pravda.sk/domace/clanok/366071-kotleba-na-vyrocie-snp-vyvesil-cierne-zastavy-kanik-poda-trestne-oznamenie/|title=Kotleba vyvesil \u010dierne z\u00e1stavy. I\u0161lo o vlajky za padl\u00fdch v SNP, tvrd\u00ed kraj|newspaper=www.pravda.sk|language=sk}}</ref>\n\nSome media outlets such as Pluska<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pluska.sk/plus-7-dni/domov/10/exkluzivne-video-lider-neonacistov-kotleba-politike-bohatne-toto-mu-strana-kupila-po-volbach.html|title=ODHALENIE Kotleba v politike bohatne. Po pol roku nov\u00e1 vila|newspaper=www.pluska.sk}}</ref> or Denn\u00edk N<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dennikn.sk/477507/polsku-zatkli-proruskeho-politika-spominaju-aj-kotlebu.html|title=V Po\u013esku zatkli prorusk\u00e9ho politika, spom\u00ednaj\u00fa aj Kotlebu|newspaper=Denn\u00edk N|language=sk-SK}}</ref> accused the party of being financed by Russian intelligence services. The Polish Internal Security Agency ([[Agencja Bezpiecze\u0144stwa Wewn\u0119trznego|ABW]]) was the first to come with this evidence after the arrest of [[Mateusz Piskorski]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://domov.sme.sk/c/20221054/bezpecnostne-organy-taja-ci-vysetruju-napojenie-kotleba-na-moskvu.html|title=Bezpe\u010dnostn\u00e9 org\u00e1ny taja, \u010di vy\u0161etruj\u00fa napojenie Kotlebu na Moskvu|last=a.s.|first=Petit Press|newspaper=domov.sme.sk|language=sk}}</ref> The party denied all of these claims, describing the party's position of neutrality in regards to the United States and Russia, but firmly opposing any aggression against Russia or its government, accusing the US of being the main sponsor of terrorism across the world and NATO of being an actual aggressor against Russia. The [[foreign policy of the United States]] is cited by the party as one of the reasons for why the party wants Slovakia to leave NATO. The other reason is the [[NATO bombing of Yugoslavia]] in 1999.\n\nOn February 2, 2017, Marian Kotleba and his party spoke against sending a contingent of 152 Slovak soldiers on a NATO training mission in Latvia near the Russian border, stating that it was a clear provocation of the [[Russian Federation]] by NATO.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.naseslovensko.net/nase-nazory/zahranicna-politika/vladna-koalicia-s-podporou-sas-a-olano-schvalila-vyslanie-slovenskeho-vojska-na-ruske-hranice/|title=Vl\u00e1dna koal\u00edcia s podporou SaS a O\u013daNO schv\u00e1lila vyslanie slovensk\u00e9ho vojska na rusk\u00e9 hranice!|newspaper=Kotleba - \u013dudov\u00e1 strana Na\u0161e Slovensko|language=sk-SK|access-date=2017-02-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171021015136/http://www.naseslovensko.net/nase-nazory/zahranicna-politika/vladna-koalicia-s-podporou-sas-a-olano-schvalila-vyslanie-slovenskeho-vojska-na-ruske-hranice/|archive-date=2017-10-21|url-status=dead}}</ref> During a voting session on this issue in the Slovak parliament, only his party and [[We Are Family (Slovakia)|SME RODINA]] voted against sending troops on the NATO mission, while every other party supported it. He also accused the government and opposition of acting like the Nazis and Adolf Hitler in 1941 when he was preparing to attack the Soviet Union before [[Operation Barbarossa]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://aktualne.atlas.sk/slovensko/politika/do-lotysska-vysleme-152-vojakov-cvicit-budu-obranu-vychodnej-hranice-nato.html|title=Do Loty\u0161ska vy\u0161leme 152 vojakov. Cvi\u010di\u0165 bud\u00fa obranu v\u00fdchodnej hranice NATO {{!}} Aktu\u00e1lne.sk|last=a.s.|first=News and Media Holding|newspaper=aktualne.sk|language=sk-SK}}</ref>\n\nOn June 2, 2017, the party was accused of being financed by Alexander Usovskij from Belarus, after his emails were leaked to the public and were reported on by German broadcaster [[ZDF]]. It is said that he was supplying money from the Russian Federation to Eastern European countries, including Slovakia, to support pro-Russian activities and political parties, even mentioning that Usovskij is supporting \u013dSNS' work. Usovskij denied that he was in any contact with \u013dSNS, but said that he sympathises with the party's activities, agreeing with their bid for a referendum to leave NATO. ZDF also added that he may have been looking for investors that could help the party's campaign in said referendum.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://hnonline.sk/slovensko/970565-bielorus-ktory-mal-posielat-na-slovensko-peniaze-z-ruska-podporujem-myslienku-kotlebu|title=Bielorus, ktor\u00fd mal posiela\u0165 na Slovensko peniaze z Ruska: Podporujem my\u0161lienku Kotlebu|newspaper=hnonline.sk|language=sk-SK}}</ref> A investigation by the National Criminal Agency (The Slovak equivalent of the FBI) found no evidence that \u013dSNS was being funded by the Russian government.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.etrend.sk/ekonomika/policajti-nakoniec-u-kotlebovcov-sponzorov-z-ruska-nenasli.html|title=Policajti nakoniec u kotlebovcov sponzorov z Ruska nena\u0161li|newspaper=etrend.sk|language=sk-SK}}</ref>\n\nDuring his presidential campaign, party leader Marian Kotleba frequently deployed slogans such as \"For Slavic brotherhood, against a war with Russia!\" on his campaign billboards. Moreover, the party's candidates for the European Parliament, such as Milan Mazurek, uttered the phrase \"For cooperation with Russia, against the sanctions!\" during their respective campaigns.  The Party firmly supports the complete cancellation of all sanctions against the Russian Federation.\n\n[[File:\u013dSNS_Rally_2019.png|right|thumb|A rally of \u013dSNS members in 2019.]]\nOn May 16, 2019, the Russian Foreign Ministry criticized the extremist policies and tactics of Kotleba-\u013dSNS.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://spravy.pravda.sk/svet/clanok/512351-moskva-odsudila-extremizmus-kotlebovcov/|title=Moskva ods\u00fadila extr\u00e9mizmus kotlebovcov|newspaper=pravda.sk|language=sk-SK}}</ref>\n\nOn July 20, 2019, freshly elected party MEP and a member of the committee for friendship with the Russian Federation, [[Miroslav Rada\u010dovsk\u00fd]],  spoke alongside [[Viktor Medvedchuk]], a well known Ukrainian conservative pro-Russian politician and oligarch, who was having a conference in the [[European Parliament]] on the topic named \"Plan for the Restoration of Peace in Ukraine\". Alongside Rada\u010dovsk\u00fd, there were also many other MEPs from other countries, such as [[Alexandra Phillips (Brexit Party politician)|Alexandra Phillips]] and [[Nathan Gill]] of the [[Brexit Party]], French MEP [[Nicolas Bay]] of [[Rassemblement National]], Spanish MEP [[Javier Nart]] of the [[Ciudadanos]] Movement, and [[Tatjana \u017ddanoka]] of the  [[Latvian Russian Union]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/sudcaradacovsky/posts/838986903153669?__xts__[0]=68.ARA1OaZFGJucqm4vZWTfmq49nt6wq-1b2IexBdLqGdd7n0HlApv8AGJtPS51JDf43nW1z2ohJcLjuuVQ8rPLaI8GXxXTqqQq8bE8ZWmBFGySoWMhAbOU7sQBJ-F45cwpnMB8NvFbJAEPiQcJt2oH0ENKo3iPQuwPCO9U9J36tFfydnbNV0pD5yre_p2JZnRcyEA_2ANOy4kcVMZ3tRMp380LkHB6G6b3ppLL6fCau2gzS3zGERfS-qyo9abD4002p4iSXEPBYAJDS9WRg0Y0f7LWwfxvfub4-H3Hql2XSnBedFBzcjvVmjvzACLIKkgLY-kx7XhLJsAKuHrgy6jbwSU&__tn__=-R|title=N/A|website=Facebook|url-access=registration}}</ref>\n\nMany members of the party are known for their sympathy towards the Russian Federation and its allies. Party leader Marian Kotleba is known for his sympathy towards the Russian Federation and the [[Syrian Arab Republic]], as evidenced by his repeated use of pro-Russian slogans during his presidential campaign and his declaration on national television that [[Bashar al-Assad]] is \"a hero of the Middle-East\". Kotleba also made trips to Syria, having met with the Syrian Speaker of the House and the Foreign Minister of Syria.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.naseslovensko.net/cinnost/reportaze-z-akcii/fotoreportaz-z-oficialnej-navstevy-mariana-kotlebu-v-syrii-a-libanone/ |title=Fotoreport\u00e1\u017e z ofici\u00e1lnej n\u00e1v\u0161tevy Mariana Kotlebu v S\u00fdrii a Libanone. Zaml\u010diavan\u00e9 inform\u00e1cie o skuto\u010dn\u00fdch agresoroch! |date=30 June 2018}}</ref> \n\nIt was revealed from the documents found within the governor's office upon Kotleba's departure from Bansk\u00e1 Bystrica's governorship that he wanted to send a letter to the Russian ambassador, in which he asked for assistance and personally wrote about his intention to buy a Russian car. MEP Milan Uhr\u00edk visited the [[People's Republic of China]] on one occasion and spoke in support of their authoritarian government. Milan Mazurek and Miroslav Rada\u010dovsk\u00fd are also known for their Russophilic views.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/feb/14/how-a-slovakian-neo-nazi-got-elected |title=How a Slovakian neo-Nazi got elected |date=14 February 2019}}</ref> Kotleba also spoke critically of American intervention in Iraq, Afghanistan, Yugoslavia, Libya, and Syria, even going as far as to list every instance of [[United States involvement in regime change]] in the [[National Council (Slovakia)|National Council]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SIDIM1x4Qag |title=M. Kotleba o NATO (6. sch\u00f4dza - 14. 6. 2016) |date=10 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn October 13, 2019, Milan Uhr\u00edk made a speech in the European Parliament about the situation in Ukraine and the ongoing conflict in Donbass, blaming the United States for orchestrating an alleged coup d'\u00e9tat in Kiev during the Euromaidan protests and the [[2014 Ukrainian Revolution]] which ousted Viktor Yanukovych, and then proceeded to condemn the United States and other western nations for supporting a war between Slavic countries such as Ukraine and Russia, stating that: \"We Slavs are not stupid and we don't need American agents, their advice or their wars\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.antipropaganda.sk/uhrik-siri-v-europskom-parlamente-proruske-dezinformacie/ |title=Uhr\u00edk \u0161\u00edri v Eur\u00f3pskom parlamente prorusk\u00e9 dezinform\u00e1cie |date=13 October 2019}}</ref>\n==Support==\nThe party gets little support in Bratislava, where anti-Kotleba slogans can be found. However the party's message resonates more in smaller towns and rural areas where people feel left behind and dislike elites.<ref name=\"fp\" />\n== Election results ==\n\n=== National Council ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Vote\n! Vote %\n! Seats\n! Place\n! Government\n|-\n| [[2010 Slovak parliamentary election|2010]]\n| 33,724 \n| 1.33\n| {{Composition bar|0|150|hex={{Kotleba \u2013 Peo