{"title_page": "Surabaya Kota railway station", "text_new": "{{unreferenced|date=December 2014}}\n{{Infobox station\n | name                = Surabaya Kota Station\n | image               = Surabaya Kota Railway Station.jpg\n | image_caption       = Entrance Surabaya Kota Station\n | image_upright       = \n | address             = [[Surabaya]], [[East Java]]\n | country             = [[Indonesia]]\n | coordinates         = {{coord|-7.243|112.741|type:railwaystation_region:ID|display=inline,title}}\n | line                = [[Surabaya railway|Surabaya Railway]]\n | other               =\n | platform            = 3\n | tracks              = 4\n | parking             = Available\n | bicycle             =\n | baggage_check       =\n | passengers          =\n | pass_year           =\n | pass_percent        =\n | pass_system         =\n | opened              =\n | rebuilt             =\n | ADA                 = Available\n | code                = SB\n | owned               = [[Indonesian Railway Company]]\n | zone                =\n | services            =\n | mpassengers         =\n | map_type            = Indonesia_Surabaya\n | map_caption         = Location in [[Surabaya]]\n | native_name         = ''{{smaller|Stasiun Surabaya Kota}}''\n | elevation           = {{convert|4|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n | structure           = Ground\n}}\n\n'''Surabaya Kota Station''' is a railway station in [[Surabaya]], [[East Java]], [[Indonesia]]. The local people usually call it Semut station. \n\n==History==\nLocated at the central of the city, the station is also the oldest railway station in Surabaya, built in 1875 and opened in 1878. The station has two buildings, the old building is located at the north-east of the newer building, whereas the new building is located at the end of the tracks. The historic old building was demolished because of mall building near the station, but the mall building process was stopped because it didn't have a building license, and the old building has been protected and chosen as one of the heritages in Surabaya.\n\nThe station still using mechanical signals to preserve its classical style and has two [[signal box]]es near the exit signal. The station was very strategic, it is located near a market that is the one of the most famous markets in Surabaya, Pasar Atum, it also located near [[Sunan Ampel]]'s tomb.\n\nThere are many train car shunting activities, especially at the morning and the evening when many trains are departing and arriving at the station. The station doesn't have a [[locomotive depot]], the locomotive depot is located at Sidotopo station located at north-east of the station. [[Surabaya Gubeng]] station is located at south-east of the station about three kilometers far. Uniquely these three stations formed a triangle shaped railway, but the railway between Surabaya Kota with Surabaya Gubeng is a [[double track]]ed railway, the others are [[single track (rail)|Single Tracks]].\n\n==Services==\nList of the trains that start and end their trip:\n*Komuter Supor to [[Porong railway station|Porong]] via [[Sidoarjo railway station|Sidoarjo]]\n*Dhoho to [[Blitar railway station|Blitar]] via [[Kertosono railway station|Kertosono]]\n*Penataran to [[Blitar railway station|Blitar]] via [[Malang railway station|Malang]]\n*Tumapel to [[Malang railway station|Malang]]\n*Lokal Ekonomi/KRD Kertosono to [[Kertosono railway station|Kertosono]]\n\n{{S-rail-start}}\n{{s-rail|title=Indonesian Railway Company}}\n{{rail line\n|previous = {{stnlnk|Surabaya Gubeng}}\n|route    = [[Surabaya railway|'''<span style=\"color: red\">Surabaya Railway</span>''']]\n|next     = ''Terminus''\n|col      = FF0000\n|term1    = {{stnlnk|Wonokromo}}\n}}\n{{rail line\n|previous = ''Terminus''\n|route    = [[Surabaya railway|'''<span style=\"color: red\">Surabaya Railway</span>''']]\n|next     = {{stnlnk|Mesigit}}\n|term2    = {{stnlnk|Kalimas}}\n|col      = FF0000\n|rows1    = 2\n}}\n{{rail line\n|previous = ''Terminus''\n|route    = [[Surabaya railway|'''<span style=\"color: red\">Surabaya Railway</span>''']]\n|next     = {{stnlnk|Sidotopo}}<br>''Terminus''\n|col      = FF0000\n|hide1    = true\n}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Train Stations in Indonesia|East Java}}\n\n[[Category:Railway stations in East Java]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Surabaya]]\n[[Category:Cultural Properties of Indonesia in East Java]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1878]]\n\n{{Indonesia-railstation-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=December 2014}}\n{{Infobox station\n | name                = Surabaya Kota Station\n | image               = Surabaya Kota Railway Station.jpg\n | image_caption       = Entrance Surabaya Kota Station\n | image_upright       = \n | address             = [[Surabaya]], [[East Java]]\n | country             = [[Indonesia]]\n | coordinates         = {{coord|-7.243|112.741|type:railwaystation_region:ID|display=inline,title}}\n | line                = [[Surabaya railway|Surabaya Railway]]\n | other               =\n | platform            = 3\n | tracks              = 4\n | parking             = Available\n | bicycle             =\n | baggage_check       =\n | passengers          =\n | pass_year           =\n | pass_percent        =\n | pass_system         =\n | opened              =\n | rebuilt             =\n | ADA                 = Available\n | code                = SB\n | owned               = [[Indonesian Railway Company]]\n | zone                =\n | services            =\n | mpassengers         =\n | map_type            = Indonesia_Surabaya\n | map_caption         = Location in [[Surabaya]]\n | native_name         = ''{{smaller|Stasiun Surabaya Kota}}''\n | elevation           = {{convert|4|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n | structure           = Ground\n}}\n\n'''Surabaya Kota Station''' is a railway station in [[Surabaya]], [[East Java]], [[Indonesia]]. The local people usually call it Semut station. \n\n==History==\nLocated at the central of the city, the station is also the oldest railway station in Surabaya, built in 1875 and opened in 1878. The station has two buildings, the old building is located at the north-east of the newer building, whereas the new building is located at the end of the tracks. The historic old building was demolished because of mall building near the station, but the mall building process was stopped because it didn't have a building license, and the old building has been protected and chosen as one of the heritages in Surabaya.\n\nThe station still using mechanical signals to preserve its classical style and has two [[signal box]]es near the exit signal. The station was very strategic, it is located near a market that is the one of the most famous markets in Surabaya, Pasar Atum, it also located near [[Sunan Ampel]]'s tomb.\n\nThere are many train car shunting activities, especially at the morning and the evening when many trains are departing and arriving at the station. The station doesn't have a [[locomotive depot]], the locomotive depot is located at Sidotopo station located at north-east of the station. [[Surabaya Gubeng]] station is located at south-east of the station about three kilometers far. Uniquely these three stations formed a triangle shaped railway, but the railway between Surabaya Kota with Surabaya Gubeng is a [[double track]]ed railway, the others are [[single track (rail)|Single Tracks]].\n\n==Services==\nList of the trains that start and end their trip:\n*Komuter Supor to [[Porong railway station|Porong]] via [[Sidoarjo railway station|Sidoarjo]]\n*Dhoho to [[Blitar railway station|Blitar]] via [[Kertosono railway station|Kertosono]]\n*Penataran to [[Blitar railway station|Blitar]] via [[Malang railway station|Malang]]\n*Tumapel to [[Malang railway station|Malang]]\n*Lokal Ekonomi/KRD Kertosono to [[Kertosono railway station|Kertosono]]\n\n{{S-rail-start}}\n{{s-rail|title=Indonesian Railway Company}}\n{{rail line\n|previous = {{stnlnk|Surabaya Gubeng}}\n|route    = [[Surabaya railway|'''<span style=\"color: red\">Surabaya Railway</span>''']]\n|next     = ''Terminus''\n|col      = FF0000\n|term1    = {{stnlnk|Wonokromo}}\n}}\n{{rail line\n|previous = ''Terminus''\n|route    = [[Surabaya railway|'''<span style=\"color: red\">Surabaya Railway</span>''']]\n|next     = {{stnlnk|Mesigit}}\n|term2    = {{stnlnk|Kalimas}}\n|col      = FF0000\n|rows1    = 2\n}}\n{{rail line\n|previous = ''Terminus''\n|route    = [[Surabaya railway|'''<span style=\"color: red\">Surabaya Railway</span>''']]\n|next     = {{stnlnk|Sidotopo}}<br>''Terminus''\n|col      = FF0000\n|hide1    = true\n}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Train Stations in Indonesia|East Java}}\n\n[[Category:Railway stations in East Java]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Surabaya]]\n[[Category:Cultural Properties of Indonesia in East Java]]\n[[Category:Transport in East Java]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1878]]\n\n{{Indonesia-railstation-stub}}\n", "name_user": "OktaRama2010", "label": "safe", "comment": "removedCategory:Transport in East JavausingHotCat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surabaya_Kota_railway_station"}
